==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Contorted
<hw>Con*tort"ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Twisted, or twisted
together.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>contorted</xex> chain of icicles.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Massinger.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Twisted back upon
itself, as some parts of plants.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Arranged so as
to overlap each other; <as>as, petals in <ex>contorted</ex> or convolute
⟦ae⟧stivation</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Contortion</ent>⟦br⟧
